text.tspan: Fibre directions, with error bars as determined
by a previous program. Multiple directions
1. An adjacent corner is selected, at random
2. A direction is selected from that corner out of
the available choices. Many options to do this,
determined by the user at start time. These
proportional to error bars, and full-out random.
3. The particle jumps a fixed distance in the
direction of the chosen fibre. The vector is
reversed if needed to keep the angle of motion
4. This process is repeated until the particle hits
a region of the brain which has been selected as
